OL,3,CGovernment addresses calls to improve
OL,4,C'outdated' animal cruelty laws
OL,6,FThe interim head of a Jersey charity
OL,7,Fsays he is working with the Government
OL,8,Fto improve "outdated" animal cruelty
OL,9,Flaws.
OL,11,FTom Noel from the JSPCA explains that
OL,12,Fhe is joining forces with the States
OL,13,FVet to improve current legislation
OL,14,Ffrom 2004 which states animals can
OL,15,Fonly be seized if their basic needs
OL,16,Fare not met, including food and water.
OL,18,FHe says other forms of neglect are
OL,19,Fmuch harder to act upon and animals
OL,20,Fneed appropriate protection.
