OL,3,CGovernment addresses calls to improve
OL,4,C'outdated' animal cruelty laws
OL,6,F"'Is it allowed to display normal
OL,7,Fanimal behaviours or is it being
OL,8,Frestricted in some way? And finally,
OL,9,Fare its emotional needs being
OL,10,Fmaintained? Is it getting walks and
OL,11,Fregular human contact?.'"
OL,13,FMr Noel believes "no one buys an
OL,14,Fanimal to mistreat it generally" and
OL,15,Fsays people are facing "hard choices"
OL,16,Fin the current economic environment.
OL,18,FHe adds: "It's quite tough out there,
OL,19,Fwe would never want to see an owner
OL,20,Fhaving to choose between feeding the
OL,21,Fchildren or feeding the animal."
